        public SubscriptionsTypes.PlacementInfo.Builder setHost(java.lang.String host)
        Host onto which the virtual machine template should be placed. If getHost() and getResourcePool() are both specified, getResourcePool() must belong to getHost(). If getHost() and getCluster() are both specified, getHost() must be a member of getCluster(). This property was added in vSphere API 6.7.2. The property will be null if the subscribed library associated with the subscription does not have a host.
